HEADWORD: Hydranth
<hw>Hy"dranth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hydra</ets> +
Gr. <?/ a flower.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the nutritive
zooids of a hydroid colony. Also applied to the proboscis or manubrium
of a hydroid medusa. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Hydroidea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

